734243f.title: Harlem River - Bronx - 138th Street (East) - Park Avenue.
734243f.text:
Harlem River, Bronx shore, south from East 138th Street to Park Ave., showing the New York State Canal Terminal and the Park Ave. Bridge of the New York Central Railroad.

November 10, 1930

P.L. Sperr
734243f.folder: 138th Street (East) - Park Avenue., Harlem River, Bronx, NY

700063f-a.text:
201 and 205-213 Eaat 138th Street (right), at and adjoining the N.E. corner of Park Ave. The 2-story brick building, No. 205-213, is occupied by the Carolyn Laundry Garage. Also shown (left) is Park Ave., at and adjoining the N.E. corner of East 138th Street.
November 29, 1936.
P. L. Sperr.
